Deployment Diagram

The deployment diagram illustrates the physical environment in which CookSnap â€“ Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images is deployed. 
It shows the hardware nodes, their responsibilities, and the connections between them.

Deployment Environment

User Device (Mobile / Web Client)
Used by users to upload grocery images, view detected ingredients, and access recipe recommendations through the CookSnap interface.

Admin System
Used by administrators to access the dashboard, manage system data, and view reports.

Application Server
Hosts the core application logic, including image processing, ingredient detection, recipe recommendation, authentication, and notification services.

Database Server
Stores user information, grocery image metadata, detected ingredients, recipes, and system logs.

Network (Internet)
Provides connectivity between user devices, admin systems, and backend servers for data exchange and system access.

This deployment diagram highlights how CookSnap components are physically distributed and connected, ensuring scalability, security, and efficient system operation.
